public class VariableMap<Value> extends BaseStringMap<Value>
A bounded map from string to value which supports variable interpolation into a string via expand(String). For example, a VariableMap of Integers might have the entries "x=9" and "y=3" in it. In this case, interpolate("${x} = ${y}") would yield the string "9 = 3". An example use of this class can be found in File.withVariables(VariableMap<?> variables), which substitutes the name of the file with values from the variable map.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)

    • expand

      public String expand​(String text, String defaultValue)
      Interpolates the values in this map into the given string. Substitutions occur when the names of variables appear inside curly braces after a '$', like "${x}". Any such substitution markers that do not correspond to a variable in the map are substituted with the given default value, or if that value is null, they are left unchanged.
      Parameters:
      text - The string to interpolate values into
      defaultValue - The value to use for missing variables, or null to leave the ${x} marker unexpanded
      Returns:
      The interpolated string

    • expanded

      public VariableMap<String> expanded()
      Returns:
      This variable map with all string values expanded by interpolating values for other keys in the map. For example, the entry for key "coordinate" might be the value "${location-x}, ${location-y}". If the value for the key "location-x" is "9" and the value for "location-y" is "81", then the expanded variable map will have the value "9, 81" for the key "coordinate"

    • withQuotedValues

      Returns:
      This variable map with all the values as quoted strings.
